Portions of this package are vendored verbatim or ported (with
adaptation for TypeScript and this package's module layout) from
@observerly/astrometry. The following modules are derivative works:

  src/util/coordinates.ts
  src/util/time.ts
    — Coordinate transforms (ecliptic ↔ equatorial ↔ horizontal),
      Julian Date, Greenwich/Local Sidereal Time, hour angle,
      obliquity of the ecliptic, sidereal-to-UT conversion.

  src/astrometry/earth/vsop87.ts
  src/astrometry/earth/orbit.ts
  src/astrometry/earth/heliocentric.ts
    — Earth VSOP87 (truncated) periodic-term tables and the
      heliocentric ecliptic position they evaluate to. Earth orbital
      record (mean elements). Eccentricity, obliquity, and
      eccentricity-coefficient polynomials.

  src/astrometry/sun/anomaly.ts
  src/astrometry/sun/ecliptic.ts
  src/astrometry/sun/equatorial.ts
  src/astrometry/sun/transit.ts
    — Solar mean / true anomaly, equation of centre, mean / true
      geometric longitude, ecliptic longitude, ecliptic and equatorial
      coordinates (with FK5 + aberration corrections), and the NOAA-
      style generalised solar transit.

  src/astrometry/moon/{mean,true,ecliptic,equatorial,distance,orbit,phase,events}.ts
    — Brown-style lunar mean and true elements, ecliptic/equatorial
      coordinates, geocentric distance, geocentric and topocentric
      angular diameter, phase angle / illumination / age, named-phase
      classifier, blue-moon predicate, and next-new / next-full search.

  src/astrometry/planets/{data,anomaly,heliocentric,geocentric,kepler}.ts
    — Mean orbital elements for Mercury through Neptune, planet mean
      and true anomaly, heliocentric L/B/R, and geocentric ecliptic
      coordinate (inferior- and superior-planet branches).

  src/astrometry/transit/{circumpolar,hourAngle,riseSet}.ts
    — Body circumpolarity / visibility / above-horizon predicates,
      rise/set hour-angle calculation, and recursive next-rise /
      next-set search with day-walk fallthrough.

  src/astrometry/constellations/data.ts
  src/astrometry/constellations/precession.ts
  src/astrometry/constellations/maths.ts
    — All 88 IAU constellation polygon FeatureCollections (data.ts is
      a verbatim copy of upstream constellations.js with imports
      rewired to point at the in-tree precession + interpolation
      helpers), Nancy Roman boundary table, and `getConstellation`
      reverse lookup. Equatorial-precession correction. Geodesic
      interpolation helpers used by the polygon builder.

